
  <div class="wrapper">

  <div id="sidebar" class="popout-sidebar">
    <%= render :partial => 'about_nav', locals: {show: 'developers'} %>
  </div>

  <div id="content" class="">
    <div class="about-block">
      <%= render :partial => 'links', :locals => {'show': 'developer'} %>
      <!-- ABOUT TESS DATA -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="odd-about-block">
          <div id='code_and_data' class="h3">For Developers</div>

          TeSS is committed to the FAIR principles. Making data findable, accessible, interoperable and re-usable. As such,
          all of the content we collect in TeSS is available under the CC-BY-4.0 licence and can be accessed
          through our API and through our widgets. The TeSS codebase is also available to re-use under the BSD Licence and can
          be found on GitHub.

          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-5 5 open-access-box">
              <div class="h2 licence-title">Software</div>
              <div class="open-access-location">
                <%= link_to 'https://github.com/ElixirTeSS/TeSS', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <div class="register-condition-graphic">
                      <%= image_tag 'about/GitHub-Mark-64px.png', class: "" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="register-condition">The sourcecode for TeSS is available on GitHub</div>
                <% end %>
              </div>
              <div class="open-access-licence">
                <%= link_to 'https://github.com/ElixirTeSS/TeSS/blob/master/LICENSE', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-code licence-logo"></i></div>
                    <div class="register-condition">It is available under the BSD-3 licence</div>
                <% end %>
              </div>
            </div>
              <div class="col-lg-5 open-access-box">
                <div class="h2 licence-title">Data</div>
                  <%= link_to developers_path(:anchor => 'api') do %>
                    <div class="open-access-location">
                      <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-plug licence-logo"></i></div>
                      <div class="register-condition">The data in TeSS can be accessed via our API</div>
                    </div>
                  <% end %>
                <div class="open-access-licence">
                  <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-database licence-logo"></i></div>
                  <%= link_to 'https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/', target: '_blank' do %>
                  <div class="register-condition">It is available under the Creative Commons CC-BY 4.0 licence</div>
                  <% end %>
                </div>
              </div>
              </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="even-about-block">
          <div class="h3" id="widgets">Widgets</div>
            <p>Widgets are chunks of javascript code that can be copied into your websites source code to display
              content from TeSS. There are several different styles and functionalities available from our configurable
              widget suite. Widgets can be used to enhance your site and offer your community a list of relevant
              events or training resources.</p>
              <p>
              Below is a live example of a TeSS widget.
              </p>
                <p><%= link_to 'https://elixirtess.github.io/TeSS_widgets/', class: 'btn btn-primary', target: '_blank' do %>
                  View Our Available Widgets
                  <% end %></p>
        <hr/>
      <link rel="stylesheet" property="stylesheet" href="https://elixirtess.github.io/TeSS_widgets/css/tess-widget.css"/>
      <div class="sub-about-block">
      <div id="tess-widget-materials-table" class="tess-widget tess-widget-faceted-table"></div>
      </div>
      <script>
      function initTeSSWidgets() {
          TessWidget.Materials(document.getElementById('tess-widget-materials-table'),
              'FacetedTable',
              {
                  opts: {
                      columns: [{name: 'Name', field: 'title'},
                          {name: 'Description', field: 'short-description'}],
                      allowedFacets: ['scientific-topics', 'target-audience']
                  },
                  params: {
                      pageSize: 5,
                      q: 'Python'
                  }
              });
      }
      </script>
      <script async="" defer="" src="https://elixirtess.github.io/TeSS_widgets/js/tess-widget-standalone.js" onload="initTeSSWidgets()"></script>
<hr>
<p>
If you do decide to include our widgets on your website, we have a mailing list you can join to keep
informed about any service disruptions, required updates, or new features
</p>
                <p><%= link_to 'https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/tess-widgets-user-group', class: 'btn btn-primary', target: '_blank' do %>
                  Join the widgets mailing list
                  <% end %></p>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="odd-about-block">
          <div class="h4" id="api">API </div>

          <span style="float:right">
                      </span>
          <span>
            <p>TeSS has a fully functioning <a href="http://jsonapi.org/" target="_blank">JSON API</a>. You can
              explore our JSON-API by adding .json_api to the URL of most pages. For example:</p>
            <p><code>
               <a href="https://tess.elixir-europe.org/materials.json_api?scientific_topics=RNA-Seq">
                 https://tess.elixir-europe.org/materials.json_api?scientific_topics=RNA-Seq </a>
            </code></p>
            <p><code>
               <a href="https://tess.elixir-europe.org/events.json_api">
                               https://tess.elixir-europe.org/events.json_api </a>
            </code></p>
            <p><code>
               <a href="https://tess.elixir-europe.org/events/data-fairification-for-data-stewards.json_api">
                  https://tess.elixir-europe.org/events/data-fairification-for-data-stewards.json_api
           </a>
            </code></p>
            <p><code>
               <a href="https://tess.elixir-europe.org/content_providers.json_api">
                               https://tess.elixir-europe.org/content_providers.json_api </a>
            </code></p>
            <p><code>
               <a href="https://tess.elixir-europe.org/workflows.json_api">
                               https://tess.elixir-europe.org/workflows.json_api </a>
            </code></p>

            <p>We recommend using our JSON API but we will also continue supporting our legacy API;
              technical information of which can be found on our <a href="https://app.swaggerhub.com/api/njall/TeSS/1.0.0/">
                          Swagger Hub Documentation</a> page </p>
                      </span>
          <%= link_to 'https://app.swaggerhub.com/api/njall/TeSS/1.0.0/', class: 'btn btn-primary', target: '_blank' do %>
              View our legacy API on SwaggerHub
              <%= image_tag 'swagger.png', size: "20x20"%>
        <% end %>
        </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <%= render :partial => 'links', :locals => {'show': 'developer'} %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>